or JDK25.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating logging dependencies**\\n\\nI'm considering if the native image might behave differently regarding logging. The existing setup adds slf4j-simple 1.5.3 for logs, but is that necessary? For tests triggering a static logger with only slf4j-api 1.5.8, there might be a NOP logger class involved. Importantly, meaningful coverage can be achieved without a binding. There’s also agent guidance to note: tests can exercise protocol types in-process, avoiding the need for Docker and environment properties. I should clarify that no environment variables are necessary.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"Add the provided-scope Servlet API for meaningful coverage of Jackrabbit WebDAV server/request/response classes; no Docker service or environment setup is indicated.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"javax.servlet:servlet-api:2.4\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"jackrabbit-webdav 2.0-beta4 declares javax.servlet:servlet-api as provided, and public classes such as AbstractWebdavServlet, WebdavRequestImpl, WebdavResponseImpl, InputContextImpl, OutputContextImpl, and header parsers reference javax.servlet/http types. Tests that exercise those APIs need the servlet classes on the test compile/runtime classpath.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No environment variables or system properties are required. The library README describes this artifact as a reusable WebDAV interfaces/utilities/client/server library rather than a deployable Jackrabbit server, so generated tests should prefer in-process XML, method, header, locator, and request/response stub coverage instead of requiring a live WebDAV or Jackrabbit repository service.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The reported native-image run failures in AbstractLocatorFactory look like version-specific behavior or assertion drift rather than missing external setup.\",\n    \"An SLF4J binding is useful only to avoid logging warnings; it is not required for meaningful coverage because slf4j-api is a normal transitive dependency.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0b8e6cd7ca6025cd016a425890abb48195ac8d048586fe5990\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 966, "output": 1033, "cacheRead": 25600, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 27599, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782732930149, "responseId": "resp_0b8e6cd7ca6025cd016a425882b14c819586f60e2a003cb4cb"}}
